<TITLE> Two women injured in Khagrachhari hillslide </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khagrachhari, July 19 (bdnews24.com)- Two women were injured in a hillslide at Shalbon Harinathpara area in Khagrachhari district Sadar at 7.30 am Thursday. Momtaz Mahal (60), wife of Rawshan Ali and her daughter-in-law Swapna Akhter (25), wife of Shahid Miah were seriously injured when in the hillslide on their kutcha house. Local villagers rescued the injured and took them to District Sadar Hospital. People of Shalbon area said, more than 500 families were living under risk on the foot and top of hills in Shalbon, harinathpara, Gep, Comilla Tila, Mehedibag, ADC Tila area of the district town. Continuous torrential rains and large scaled cutting of hills have increased the risk of hill slide. b
